            <bug_when>2012-01-17 08:03:06 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Using the portable testrunner and its API for a while, I realized that i group my testes into logical units by defining a test class for each logical set. Seeing this in the code, an annotating comment on top of each define explains the scope of the tests. But during the execution, this comment is not visible and the scope is lost. Instead of adding a comment on top, we should provide a way to name the test classes which will then be displayed in the testrunner and gives the tester the complete scope during test execution.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
